post_text: Battle Lake Public School is excited to announce an opening for a full-time health aide for the upcoming 2020-2021 school year. The position will work 7 hours per day/173 days per year. Battle Lake Public School is an award winning school, a great place for students to learn, and located in the heart of lake and recreation opportunities. Applicants should send a letter of interest, resume, and 3 letters of recommendation along with a completed application form; which can be found in the district office or on the district website to Superintendent Darren Kern at 402 Summit ST W Battle Lake MN 56515 or dkern@isd542.org. This posting will be open until filled.

text:
Battle Lake Public School is excited to announce an opening for a full-time health aide for the upcoming 2020-2021 school year. The position will work 7 hours per day/173 days per year. Battle Lake Public School is an award winning school, a great place for students to learn, and located in the heart of lake and recreation opportunities. Applicants should send a letter of interest, resume, and 3 letters of recommendation along with a completed application form; which can be found in the district office or on the district website to Superintendent Darren Kern at 402 Summit ST W Battle Lake MN 56515 or dkern@isd542.org. This posting will be open until filled.

Battle Lake 542 Education Foundation
VIRTUAL 5K/10K Run & Walk

LAST DAY TO REGISTER!
Saturday, July 25, 2020

Today is the last day to register for the upcoming VIRTUAL race! Battle Lake Students need your help and support! All registered participants are eligible for prizes!

This year’s annual race will be hosted virtually! Purchase a t-shirt to register your name for the 5k/10k run/walk. Participants who purchase a shirt are eligible for drawings. Participants who complete the race via Strava will be eligible to win: fastest 5k/10k female, fastest 5k/10k male, and greatest elevation change. You do not have to complete the race to be eligible for drawings. You are REQUIRED to purchase a shirt to be eligible for Strava Prizes.

ALL the proceeds from this race will be used to help enrich Battle Lake Public School students.

Register Today!
www.bonfire.com/542-virtual-5k10k

Location:
ANYWHERE!

For more information:
https://542foundation.com/?page_id=1052

post_text: Battle Lake Public Schools will have an open School Board seat beginning July 1, 2020. If you are interested in serving on the School Board, please submit your letter of interest to School Board Chair Paul Ness via the schools address 402 Summit ST W Battle Lake, MN 56515 no later than July 3, 2020. The School Board will appoint one new member from the letters of interest they receive at their July 13th regular School Board meeting. This appointment is through December, the seat will be up for election in November to complete the remainder of the 2 year term.

post_text: Battle Lake High School will have virtual conferences tomorrow April 1st. Expect a call from one of our teachers between 4-8 pm. Some of our teachers will be calling from home so there will be no caller ID information provided with the phone call. This contact will not necessarily contain any specific information about your student(s). This will be an opportunity for Battle Lake School to connect with our families, provide an avenue for us to share information, and allow parents to ask questions.

Good
Morning

Following the message from The Governor, Battle Lake Schools will close beginning Tuesday March 17th. We will hold school on Monday so we can get devices into student hands and explain procedures while school is closed. I will be sending out more information to families later today after district leadership team has met and put a plan in place
Thank you
Superintendent Kern
